ang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Conclusion</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1656945427481" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1656945427481" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The difference between weightlifting belt vs powerlifting belt is that the former promotes stability for heavier lifts while the latter provides support during complex and larger movements. The discussion above should help you in looking for the right lifting belt for you.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Let us know any thoughts or questions you have in mind in the comment section below.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1658464143311" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1658464143311" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/c71bc6f9-1bb3-46e7-9a9a-fe5a81408cac/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Untitled-1.jpg" alt="Athlete Wearing Weightlifting Belt" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="3000" height="2000" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="3000" natural-height="2000"></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" dat